736
01:07:11.650 --> 01:07:12.850
Are you alright for money?

737
01:07:14.490 --> 01:07:17.250
Better leave you some money and,
uh...


738
01:07:22.570 --> 01:07:24.930
Whew. Say,
it's frightfully hot in here. Ahem.


739
01:07:26.970 --> 01:07:30.170
Mind if I open the window?
Get some air in.


740
01:07:32.490 --> 01:07:34.490
(window rattling)
Ah. It's better.


741
01:07:34.610 --> 01:07:36.690
Now, where's your handbag, hmm?

742
01:07:41.010 --> 01:07:42.090
Now, look here.

743
01:07:42.850 --> 01:07:46.410
Do go and dine somewhere decent,
for godsake. Hmm?


744
01:07:47.890 --> 01:07:50.570
Lois is expecting you
on Saturday. You know that.


745
01:07:50.690 --> 01:07:53.010
- Oh, she is, is she?
- She certainly is.


746
01:07:53.130 --> 01:07:54.330
And so am I.

747
01:07:55.090 --> 01:07:57.810
- Why should I be a butt
for Lois and her friends?


748
01:07:58.450 --> 01:08:00.730
She wants me there
so she can talk at me,


749
01:08:00.850 --> 01:08:02.490
so she can watch
for the right moment


750
01:08:02.650 --> 01:08:04.010
to put her enormous foot down!

751
01:08:04.130 --> 01:08:06.970
- You talk the most awful
nonsense sometimes, don't you?


752
01:08:07.090 --> 01:08:09.770
- Aren't Lois's feet enormous?

753
01:08:09.890 --> 01:08:11.850
Huge, big feet like puddles?

754
01:08:11.970 --> 01:08:13.730
(laughing)

755
01:08:18.250 --> 01:08:19.770
Alright, I'll come.

756
01:08:21.890 --> 01:08:23.770
What's it matter, anyway?

757
01:08:30.690 --> 01:08:32.610
- I hate
having to explain things.


758
01:08:35.610 --> 01:08:37.330
I hate having to talk
about things.


759
01:08:39.210 --> 01:08:41.850
Surely you must see
that you can't let Lois down.


760
01:08:43.010 --> 01:08:44.650
- What about letting me down?

761
01:08:46.250 --> 01:08:48.290
- We must keep up appearances.

762
01:08:49.490 --> 01:08:51.210
We must play the game.

763
01:08:53.530 --> 01:08:54.730
Savage.

764
01:08:56.770 --> 01:08:58.090
Bolshevist.

765
01:08:59.690 --> 01:09:02.210
You'll end up in Red Russia.
That's what'll happen to you.


766
01:09:03.810 --> 01:09:06.690
- It's horrible when someone
has no self-control,


767
01:09:06.810 --> 01:09:09.090
the consequences
for everyone else around.


768
01:09:09.210 --> 01:09:10.250
- She was pretty.

769
01:09:10.370 --> 01:09:12.250
- Mm. She tried to kill herself
at least twice.


770
01:09:12.370 --> 01:09:14.730
And that was ages
before we even knew her.


771
01:09:14.890 --> 01:09:16.450
Once,
she tried to cut her throat.


772
01:09:17.130 --> 01:09:20.450
I didn't put the scar in, of course,
but one could distinctly see it.


773
01:09:22.490 --> 01:09:24.370
(French chatter)

774
01:09:52.130 --> 01:09:53.690
(bell tolling)

775
01:10:37.530 --> 01:10:39.490
"It's as if all the blood
in my body


776
01:10:39.610 --> 01:10:42.410
is being drained very slowly,

777
01:10:42.530 --> 01:10:44.130
all the time.

778
01:10:44.810 --> 01:10:46.530
All the blood in my heart.

779
01:10:47.930 --> 01:10:50.330
What can I say
to make you believe me?"


780
01:10:51.690 --> 01:10:53.210
- You're right, of course.

781
01:10:54.650 --> 01:10:57.010
It's my fault
for getting involved


782
01:10:57.130 --> 01:10:58.650
with these neurasthenics.

783
01:11:01.930 --> 01:11:04.130
But it's not I
who seek them out.


784
01:11:05.450 --> 01:11:06.970
They who find me.

785
01:11:25.610 --> 01:11:28.250
It's as if they sensed
a weakness in me that...


786
01:11:30.050 --> 01:11:31.370
...they fasten onto.

787
01:12:09.850 --> 01:12:12.610
- Ah, Mar ya! Hello, my dear.

788
01:12:12.730 --> 01:12:15.130
Now, you just pop upstairs,
put on something warm,


789
01:12:15.250 --> 01:12:17.410
we'll go out
and have a lovely day together, huh?


790
01:12:17.570 --> 01:12:18.730
- Who sent you?

791
01:12:19.330 --> 01:12:21.730
- Sent me?
I've come to take you out.


792
01:12:31.770 --> 01:12:33.650
(bird calls)

793
01:12:45.890 --> 01:12:47.890
- Lois sent you, didn't she?

794
01:12:50.730 --> 01:12:54.330
- She thought you might be seedy
when she got your letter to them.


795
01:12:56.330 --> 01:12:58.090
- My letter to them?

796
01:12:58.610 --> 01:13:01.890
- You did write to them,
didn't you, saying you were ill or something?


797
01:13:02.730 --> 01:13:04.690
- You mean she read my letter?

798
01:13:05.530 --> 01:13:07.290
My letter to H.J.?

799
01:13:10.930 --> 01:13:12.410
- I find...

800
01:13:13.330 --> 01:13:16.810
don't you, that married people
often have rather strange relationships?


801
01:13:17.410 --> 01:13:19.490
Everyone thinks they're on the point
of breaking up,


802
01:13:19.610 --> 01:13:21.610
and then it turns out
they're thicker than ever.


803
01:13:22.250 --> 01:13:24.450
Of course, you'd know
better than I do,


804
01:13:24.570 --> 01:13:26.010
being married yourself.

805
01:13:31.250 --> 01:13:32.490
Lois...

806
01:13:34.210 --> 01:13:35.930
...Is a very rare person.

807
01:13:37.010 --> 01:13:38.810
I'm very, very fond of her.

808
01:13:40.570 --> 01:13:43.970
If I were to tell you everything
she's been through with him...


809
01:13:45.610 --> 01:13:48.810
I don't know why she puts up
with him, really. Do you?


810
01:13:49.930 --> 01:13:52.530
But that's the sort of person
she is.


811
01:13:52.650 --> 01:13:54.410
(clucking tongue)
Come on.


812
01:13:59.370 --> 01:14:01.130
Really, don't you think...

813
01:14:01.250 --> 01:14:04.850
Honestly, don't you think women
are truly superior beings?


814
01:14:06.330 --> 01:14:08.330
I only have to think
of my own parents.


815
01:14:09.170 --> 01:14:11.650
Father -
very charming and all that,


816
01:14:11.810 --> 01:14:14.010
but weak, shiftless.

817
01:14:14.690 --> 01:14:17.650
Oh, we children were on Mother's side.
Absolutely.


818
01:14:18.930 --> 01:14:21.090
I suppose that's made me
the way I am.


819
01:14:24.290 --> 01:14:27.370
I can't bear to see a woman
taken advantage of,


820
01:14:27.730 --> 01:14:31.370
whether it's you or Lois or...
whoever.


821
01:14:34.450 --> 01:14:35.810
What a beast.

822
01:14:42.690 --> 01:14:45.050
She's most extraordinarily fond
of you.


823
01:14:46.450 --> 01:14:47.890
She thinks about you,

824
01:14:48.610 --> 01:14:50.050
wants to help you.

825
01:14:52.130 --> 01:14:55.490
Ah. Really fears...
for you sometimes.


826
01:14:56.610 --> 01:15:00.050
But I told her that basically
you're quite a sensible sort of person.


827
01:15:00.810 --> 01:15:02.810
You wouldn't
ever do anything silly.


828
01:15:03.930 --> 01:15:07.650
- So Lois has sent you
to make sure I don't kill myself,


829
01:15:07.770 --> 01:15:10.010
like the other girl.
(laughing)


830
01:15:11.330 --> 01:15:12.970
- You mustn't get hysterical.

831
01:15:17.090 --> 01:15:18.410
You really mustn't.

832
01:15:33.250 --> 01:15:34.850
(creaking)

833
01:15:38.570 --> 01:15:40.850
(gong ringing)

834
01:15:59.930 --> 01:16:02.130
(dissonant music)

835
01:16:02.250 --> 01:16:04.090
(up-tempo music)

836
01:16:10.770 --> 01:16:14.090
- I didn't like those dark
circles around your eyes.


837
01:16:14.210 --> 01:16:15.290
(background chatter)

838
01:16:15.410 --> 01:16:18.010
I hope you haven't been
overdoing anything.


839
01:16:18.930 --> 01:16:20.890
- She was singing
an English parody!


840
01:16:25.130 --> 01:16:28.010
- ...French are like, sometimes.
- I hate people who try


841
01:16:28.130 --> 01:16:31.090
to get by with nothing
but their sensitivity.


842
01:16:42.770 --> 01:16:44.410
- Your sensitivity, what is it?

843
01:16:44.850 --> 01:16:48.810
Clergymen's daughters with long,
slim fingers and no money.


844
01:16:49.570 --> 01:16:52.650
- Don't worry.
They're getting killed off slowly.


845
01:17:10.170 --> 01:17:12.290
- I say, a riddle.

846
01:17:13.050 --> 01:17:15.730
Why is love like Rasputin?

847
01:17:22.010 --> 01:17:25.170
- Why do you want money?
- Stephan is coming out next week.


848
01:17:25.890 --> 01:17:27.530
- If you go back
to your husband,


849
01:17:27.770 --> 01:17:29.730
I can't see you again.
You understand that?


850
01:17:30.450 --> 01:17:32.970
- Are you going to try and stop me,
you and your damned Lois?!


851
01:17:33.090 --> 01:17:34.610
- What... what's the matter?

852
01:17:34.730 --> 01:17:36.850
- She's getting worked up again.
Her husband's coming out.


853
01:17:37.410 --> 01:17:39.890
Your husband will be expelled
from France.


854
01:17:41.330 --> 01:17:44.370
He'll go to Brussels and then
to Amsterdam, from pillar to post.


855
01:17:44.930 --> 01:17:47.090
Then he'll try and get back to Paris,
where they'll arrest him again.


856
01:17:47.210 --> 01:17:49.530
Now, is that the sort of life
you want to share with him?


857
01:17:49.650 --> 01:17:51.250
- And what sort of life
do you think


858
01:17:51.370 --> 01:17:53.690
I'm going to share with you
and her?!


859
01:17:54.090 --> 01:17:56.090
- I'm not going
to have my party spoiled.


860
01:17:59.890 --> 01:18:02.170
- Were you trying
to borrow money from him?


861
01:18:08.850 --> 01:18:11.330
- Why don't you give it to me?
You should want to.


862
01:18:13.650 --> 01:18:16.410
- Well, H.J. calls the shots,
you know.


863
01:18:21.170 --> 01:18:25.570
- Why is love... like Rasputin?

864
01:18:27.290 --> 01:18:30.490
Why is love... like Rasputin?

865
01:18:30.650 --> 01:18:32.290
- I haven't the faintest idea.

866
01:18:33.010 --> 01:18:35.730
- Because... you can...

867
01:18:37.610 --> 01:18:38.970
...poison it...

868
01:18:39.690 --> 01:18:41.290
and you can...

869
01:18:41.650 --> 01:18:43.050
stab it!

870
01:18:43.410 --> 01:18:44.490
And you can...

871
01:18:45.010 --> 01:18:46.810
knock it down in the mud...

872
01:18:48.250 --> 01:18:50.170
...and it will always
get up again.


873
01:18:50.290 --> 01:18:51.370
- Ha!

874
01:18:52.210 --> 01:18:53.850
- Well, don't you think
that's good?


875
01:18:54.770 --> 01:18:56.450
Don't you think that's funny?

876
01:19:00.290 --> 01:19:01.690
Love will not die.

877
01:19:03.450 --> 01:19:05.010
It simply will not die.

878
01:19:07.530 --> 01:19:08.850
Just like Rasputin.

879
01:19:23.890 --> 01:19:25.650
(birdsong)

880
01:19:34.490 --> 01:19:36.290
- Why is your hair so long?

881
01:19:36.410 --> 01:19:39.650
- The barber there always lets
people grow it before they come out.


882
01:19:40.330 --> 01:19:41.650
Decent of him.

883
01:19:44.850 --> 01:19:47.410
A lot of the wardens
are quite decent types.


884
01:19:48.370 --> 01:19:49.850
They do their work.

885
01:19:49.970 --> 01:19:52.090
I expect they'd prefer
to do something else.


886
01:19:53.330 --> 01:19:54.530
Now what do you wish?

887
01:19:56.170 --> 01:19:57.530
An éclair?

888
01:19:58.170 --> 01:19:59.770
Choux a la creme?

889
01:20:00.210 --> 01:20:02.530
Meringue? The ones you like!

890
01:20:03.250 --> 01:20:04.970
- But I can't eat
all those cakes.


891
01:20:05.090 --> 01:20:08.050
- But you must.
Mado, you don't look well.


892
01:20:09.130 --> 01:20:10.770
You haven't been eating
properly.


893
01:20:11.490 --> 01:20:13.570
You haven't been taking care
of yourself.


894
01:20:13.690 --> 01:20:14.890
Now, come on.

895
01:20:21.010 --> 01:20:23.450
I'll be able to stay four days
in Paris.


896
01:20:24.490 --> 01:20:28.450
A type I left Fresnes with this morning
may be able to lend me some money.


897
01:20:28.570 --> 01:20:30.530
Bernadet. Marcel Bernadet.

898
01:20:31.490 --> 01:20:33.010
Lives with a girl in Montmartre.

899
01:20:33.490 --> 01:20:35.250
She was there to see him
this morning.


900
01:20:35.370 --> 01:20:38.290
A bit cold it seems,
but she's a good girl.


901
01:20:38.410 --> 01:20:41.770
Huh. She was so pleased
to see him, she cried.


902
01:20:41.890 --> 01:20:43.250
Ah.

903
01:20:44.690 --> 01:20:46.930
The fun of that man is women,
you know.


904
01:20:48.330 --> 01:20:50.130
You've got some cream
on your lip.


905
01:20:57.250 --> 01:20:58.410
I don't blame you.

906
01:21:02.770 --> 01:21:05.130
- Will you just be kind to me
for a little?


907
01:21:09.570 --> 01:21:12.850
- A year in jail doesn't make
a man appetizing, huh?


908
01:21:14.810 --> 01:21:16.610
(background chatter)

909
01:21:25.050 --> 01:21:27.770
- That'll be Schlamovitz
arguing with his lady friend.


910
01:21:28.690 --> 01:21:30.970
Still, it's nice of him
to let me stay here.


911
01:21:31.610 --> 01:21:34.210
He was in there with me.
Came out two weeks ago.


912
01:21:36.850 --> 01:21:37.970
Pierre.

913
01:22:00.850 --> 01:22:01.970
Pity.

914
01:22:15.690 --> 01:22:17.010
Transparent soaps.

915
01:22:27.690 --> 01:22:29.050
Skin food.

916
01:22:38.130 --> 01:22:39.690
A very good business.

917
01:22:53.450 --> 01:22:57.290
- I know a type who makes
a fortune every three years in the Argentine.


918
01:23:00.530 --> 01:23:02.610
Then he comes to Paris
to spend it, the fool.


919
01:23:03.530 --> 01:23:05.250
My God. Paris.

920
01:23:22.690 --> 01:23:24.370
- Yes.

921
01:23:24.530 --> 01:23:27.890
Provided you turn your back on the towns
and go right out in the country.


922
01:23:33.370 --> 01:23:35.890
- But you can't ride.
- I can always learn.


923
01:23:41.570 --> 01:23:43.050
- Yes.

924
01:23:43.170 --> 01:23:45.730
In charge of accounts.
(woman laughing)


925
01:23:47.050 --> 01:23:49.530
- Do you think you could get
a job like that?


926
01:23:51.010 --> 01:23:52.410
- I need a haircut.

927
01:24:10.210 --> 01:24:12.770
- I met her one night
at the Moulin de la Galette.


928
01:24:12.890 --> 01:24:15.450
She had nowhere to go,
so I brought her home.


929
01:24:26.610 --> 01:24:28.170
(man shouting)

930
01:24:41.090 --> 01:24:45.450
- Hmm.
You have very nice, soft hair, monsieur.


931
01:24:46.770 --> 01:24:49.810
I'm glad you don't use pomade.
Not like that one.


932
01:24:49.930 --> 01:24:52.450
Makes you sick,
so much pomade.


933
01:24:53.770 --> 01:24:56.130
- If I tell you he has to leave Paris
as quickly as possible,


934
01:24:56.290 --> 01:24:57.810
I say it for his sake.

935
01:25:00.890 --> 01:25:03.730
A man thinks: I'm quite safe;

936
01:25:03.850 --> 01:25:06.010
nobody's bothering about me.

937
01:25:06.170 --> 01:25:10.090
He goes out and someone who knows him
sees him on the boulevard...


938
01:25:15.170 --> 01:25:17.610
- You've been very kind to him,
Mr. Schlamovitz.


939
01:25:18.290 --> 01:25:19.610
Thank you.

940
01:25:25.970 --> 01:25:28.010
We worked together
in the library there.


941
01:25:28.610 --> 01:25:30.370
They have some
very fascinating books.


942
01:25:30.530 --> 01:25:33.730
You would be surprised.
One can get an education


943
01:25:34.610 --> 01:25:37.010
- I had a friend who went to Berlin
when he came out.


944
01:25:38.090 --> 01:25:39.810
He did very well there.

945
01:25:40.250 --> 01:25:42.770
- I was thinking more
of Amsterdam.


946
01:25:43.050 --> 01:25:45.450
- Well, Amsterdam can be nice,
too.


947
01:25:45.570 --> 01:25:47.930
- I thought you were
so enchanted with Paris.


948
01:25:48.570 --> 01:25:52.610
- Well, every place can be nice
with a nice friend.


949
01:25:53.930 --> 01:25:55.290
(lively music playing)

950
01:25:55.410 --> 01:25:56.730
- They are late.

951
01:25:58.250 --> 01:26:00.130
Are we sure we want to do this?

952
01:26:01.970 --> 01:26:03.090
My poor H.J.

953
01:26:04.530 --> 01:26:07.130
- I thought we decided that
we were going to see it through.


954
01:26:18.170 --> 01:26:21.050
- Don't let's go.
- But they're waiting for us.


955
01:26:21.730 --> 01:26:24.210
I don't care. I want to be able
to thank your friends.


956
01:26:24.970 --> 01:26:26.330
- I don't want to see them.

957
01:26:26.890 --> 01:26:28.530
I don't want them to see you.

958
01:26:28.930 --> 01:26:30.250
- Naturally not.

959
01:26:30.850 --> 01:26:32.650
- It's they
who are not good enough.


960
01:26:35.210 --> 01:26:36.210
- Stephan...

961
01:26:37.570 --> 01:26:39.610
...wherever you're going,
don't go without me.


962
01:26:41.570 --> 01:26:43.730
- I only have just enough
for my own fare.


963
01:26:44.570 --> 01:26:47.730
- I'll borrow some money from the Heidlers,
and then I can go with you.


964
01:26:52.810 --> 01:26:55.130
Why not? Why not?

965
01:26:55.250 --> 01:26:57.090
- I must get away.

966
01:26:57.210 --> 01:26:58.970
I've lost my luck.

967
01:26:59.770 --> 01:27:02.450
- We always said we'd be together
when you came out.


968
01:27:03.410 --> 01:27:06.930
- You don't come out.
Nobody ever comes out.


969
01:27:19.410 --> 01:27:22.970
- For godsake, ask the waiter
for another fine. I'm so thirsty.


970
01:27:23.090 --> 01:27:25.250
- Don't have brandy, Mado.
She oughtn't to drink brandy.


971
01:27:26.930 --> 01:27:29.050
- I'm afraid you must come.
- You're coming back with us, aren't you?


972
01:27:29.170 --> 01:27:30.850
We'll drop you off
at your hotel.


973
01:27:30.970 --> 01:27:32.450
- You're very kind, monsieur.
I'll take her home.


974
01:27:32.610 --> 01:27:35.250
- No, no, no, I think she should come
with us. It's all on the way.


975
01:27:36.170 --> 01:27:37.330
- Let's dance.

976
01:27:54.170 --> 01:27:55.890
- You've done so much
for my wife, madame.


977
01:27:56.050 --> 01:27:56.970
You are very kind.

978
01:27:57.690 --> 01:27:59.570
There's nothing I can do
to thank you.


979
01:28:00.130 --> 01:28:01.850
- But you don't need me
to tell you


980
01:28:01.970 --> 01:28:03.850
that she's a very highly strung girl.

981
01:28:04.690 --> 01:28:06.490
There have been difficulties.

982
01:28:06.610 --> 01:28:09.490
One has had to protect her,
rather.


983
01:28:09.610 --> 01:28:13.010
- Against whom?
- Against herself, principally.


984
01:28:14.330 --> 01:28:17.290
We've seen too many girls left alone
to drift around Paris.


985
01:28:17.410 --> 01:28:20.170
- Yes.
People take advantage of them.


986
01:28:21.690 --> 01:28:23.730
- So it all comes down
to a question of money.


987
01:28:24.210 --> 01:28:25.730
I might've known with you!

988
01:28:25.850 --> 01:28:29.930
- Do look at H.J.
He can't dance and he hates it.


989
01:28:31.290 --> 01:28:33.850
I don't know
why he's doing it with her.


990
01:28:34.250 --> 01:28:35.050
Do you?

991
01:28:35.450 --> 01:28:37.410
- I expect you can tell me.

992
01:28:38.690 --> 01:28:41.450
Don't forget... 
I've been away.

993
01:28:42.130 --> 01:28:44.370
- I'm the last person to be able
to forget that,


994
01:28:44.490 --> 01:28:46.530
Monsieur... Zelli.

995
01:28:53.250 --> 01:28:56.170
Let's just sit here
and wait for them, shall we?


996
01:28:56.290 --> 01:28:57.690
- You've made a mistake, madame.

997
01:28:58.210 --> 01:29:00.210
I'm not the type to sit and wait.

998
01:29:02.610 --> 01:29:04.290
- I've had to long enough.

999
01:29:09.690 --> 01:29:11.570
- I've never shared a woman
in my life,


1000
01:29:11.690 --> 01:29:14.370
and now to have to share her
with someone like that.


1001
01:29:14.490 --> 01:29:16.410
He smells of jail.

1002
01:29:16.530 --> 01:29:18.330
- Oh, you disgust me.

1003
01:29:20.730 --> 01:29:22.450
- I have a horror of you.

1004
01:29:23.130 --> 01:29:25.170
When I think of you,
I feel sick!


1005
01:29:25.290 --> 01:29:26.890
(Mar ya laughing)

1006
01:29:27.010 --> 01:29:28.650
- Don't let her
stew up our game.


1007
01:29:30.250 --> 01:29:32.010
- What is it
that you want of me?


1008
01:29:32.930 --> 01:29:35.330
I told you I have to leave Paris
very soon.


1009
01:29:35.930 --> 01:29:37.250
- Take her with you.

1010
01:29:38.690 --> 01:29:40.490
Don't you see what will happen?

1011
01:29:41.050 --> 01:29:42.650
- That's between
the three of you.


1012
01:29:42.770 --> 01:29:44.050
- She is your wife.

1013
01:29:44.570 --> 01:29:46.450
- I carry very little
when I travel.


1014
01:29:47.010 --> 01:29:50.090
- That must be very convenient,
but not everyone can do it.


1015
01:29:50.850 --> 01:29:52.810
Some of us have to put up
with things.


1016
01:29:52.930 --> 01:29:54.210
- Well, I wouldn't.

1017
01:29:54.490 --> 01:29:57.770
I'm used to living in a decent way
among decent people.


1018
01:30:00.730 --> 01:30:02.570
- You know the conditions.

1019
01:30:02.690 --> 01:30:05.690
- As if I could...
leave him that way.


1020
01:30:05.810 --> 01:30:08.650
- It's all so abominably sordid.

1021
01:30:09.250 --> 01:30:10.490
And pitiful.

1022
01:30:11.770 --> 01:30:12.730
Pitiful.

1023
01:30:13.770 --> 01:30:15.450
- You should stay with Lois.

1024
01:30:16.810 --> 01:30:18.370
Just be with her.

1025
01:30:19.770 --> 01:30:21.170
She's your sort.

1026
01:30:21.850 --> 01:30:23.610
- Don't you think I long to?

1027
01:30:23.730 --> 01:30:25.530
So that I can be rid of you
once and for all.


1028
01:30:26.290 --> 01:30:29.330
And let you stay with your sort,
your convict husband.


1029
01:30:32.010 --> 01:30:34.010
(exclaiming)
(murmurings)


1030
01:30:35.450 --> 01:30:36.490
Ah.

1031
01:30:42.530 --> 01:30:44.810
Don't you think it's time
we rejoined our companions?


1032
01:31:21.490 --> 01:31:22.890
He went off, did he?

1033
01:31:23.490 --> 01:31:24.850
- He went off.

1034
01:31:27.490 --> 01:31:28.730
- Thank God.

1035
01:31:34.930 --> 01:31:36.890
(background chatter)

1036
01:32:21.090 --> 01:32:22.650
- Are you going alone?

1037
01:32:27.130 --> 01:32:28.610
I've had enough, too!

1038
01:32:28.730 --> 01:32:30.450
Up to here!

1039
01:32:51.370 --> 01:32:52.650
- So now we know.

1040
01:32:54.170 --> 01:32:56.130
- You've got to take me away
with you.


1041
01:32:56.890 --> 01:32:58.290
Away from them.

1042
01:32:59.170 --> 01:33:00.490
Please help me.

1043
01:33:01.370 --> 01:33:03.330
- You must think
I'm Jesus Christ.


1044
01:33:04.730 --> 01:33:06.650
So all the time you came
to visit me in jail,


1045
01:33:06.770 --> 01:33:07.930
you were Heidler's mistress.

1046
01:33:08.050 --> 01:33:10.810
You just came to laugh at me,
well put away behind the bars.


1047
01:33:13.330 --> 01:33:14.890
- Don't leave me, Stephan.

1048
01:33:16.930 --> 01:33:18.490
You're all I have.

1049
01:33:19.770 --> 01:33:20.890
Please.

1050
01:33:22.170 --> 01:33:23.530
Help me.

1051
01:33:23.650 --> 01:33:25.170
(Stephan muttering)

1052
01:33:27.530 --> 01:33:28.690
- Tell me...

1053
01:33:29.610 --> 01:33:31.330
when you were living
in the hotel...


1054
01:33:32.170 --> 01:33:33.770
Heidler came to visit you.

1055
01:33:34.410 --> 01:33:36.930
When did he come? Huh? Often?

1056
01:33:37.050 --> 01:33:38.570
(sniffling)
- No!


1057
01:33:38.690 --> 01:33:40.850
I don't remember.
It doesn't matter!!


1058
01:33:40.970 --> 01:33:42.490
- It doesn't matter.

1059
01:33:43.890 --> 01:33:45.450
You're funny, you.

1060
01:33:45.610 --> 01:33:47.730
You have a special way
of looking at things.


1061
01:33:48.570 --> 01:33:50.690
- He said he
had a horror of me.

1062
01:33:50.810 --> 01:33:53.170
And when he thought of me,
he felt sick.


1063
01:33:56.610 --> 01:33:58.370
Be kind to me, Stephan.

1064
01:33:59.330 --> 01:34:00.610
Be good to me.

1065
01:34:01.690 --> 01:34:04.330
Because I'm unhappy that I think
I'm going to die of it.


1066
01:34:04.450 --> 01:34:06.530
- Unhappy?
Of course you're unhappy.


1067
01:34:08.770 --> 01:34:11.970
Can't you see that this man,
who is at the end of his love,


1068
01:34:12.090 --> 01:34:14.010
this bag of bluff,

1069
01:34:14.130 --> 01:34:17.210
he just wants you as a sort of dessert
to finish off his meal?


1070
01:34:20.690 --> 01:34:22.170
My poor Mado.

1071
01:34:23.210 --> 01:34:24.490
Poor Mado.

1072
01:34:24.610 --> 01:34:27.250
- No, don't touch me.
Don't kiss me.


1073
01:34:27.770 --> 01:34:30.170
That isn't what I want.
- Then what is it you want?


1074
01:34:33.850 --> 01:34:35.210
Alright, I'll help you.

1075
01:34:36.530 --> 01:34:37.410
Only, do this.

1076
01:34:37.530 --> 01:34:39.770
Send a pneumatique to Heidler,
tell him to come here.


1077
01:34:39.890 --> 01:34:43.010
Say you have to speak to him urgently.
Go on, do it now.


1078
01:34:43.890 --> 01:34:45.610
- And then?
- Then [I'll be waiting for him.


1079
01:34:46.610 --> 01:34:48.570
- You must be mad.
- He's made a fool of you.


1080
01:34:48.690 --> 01:34:50.570
He forgot me when he did that.

1081
01:34:50.690 --> 01:34:52.130
I'll be waiting for him.

1082
01:34:53.010 --> 01:34:54.970
I'll jump on him from behind the door
and break his back!


1083
01:34:55.090 --> 01:34:57.450
- You are mad!
- Go on, send a pneumatique.


1084
01:34:57.570 --> 01:34:59.130
I'll come with you.

1085
01:34:59.250 --> 01:35:01.810
- No!
- You poor thing, you.


1086
01:35:02.490 --> 01:35:04.250
What fools women are.

1087
01:35:05.330 --> 01:35:07.930
And it isn't only that they are
beasts and traitors,


1088
01:35:08.050 --> 01:35:09.450
but they are such fools!

1089
01:35:10.250 --> 01:35:12.730
Well, stay here and weep.
I'll go and find Heidler myself.


1090
01:35:12.850 --> 01:35:14.130
Look here. You see this?

1091
01:35:14.850 --> 01:35:17.130
You thought I was well put away
behind the bars.


1092
01:35:17.850 --> 01:35:20.090
Wait a bit. Let me pass.

1093
01:35:20.210 --> 01:35:21.250
- No!
- Let me pass!


1094
01:35:21.410 --> 01:35:23.130
- No! you think
I'd let you touch him?!


1095
01:35:23.290 --> 01:35:25.410
I love him. I love him!

1096
01:35:25.530 --> 01:35:27.970
You think I care for you?
Not this much!


1097
01:35:28.090 --> 01:35:31.170
It's him. I love him! Heidler!

1098
01:35:31.290 --> 01:35:32.570
- Will you get away
from that door?


1099
01:35:32.690 --> 01:35:35.530
- You shan't go!
If you go, I'll call the police!


1100
01:35:35.650 --> 01:35:38.290
I'll go straight to the police station
and give you up!!


1101
01:35:38.930 --> 01:35:39.810
No!

1102
01:36:05.930 --> 01:36:07.850
- Ah!
(sniffling)


1103
01:36:26.370 --> 01:36:27.330
- Take me with you.

1104
01:36:27.450 --> 01:36:29.290
- No, I don't want anyone.
I'm late. Please leave me alone.


1105
01:36:29.410 --> 01:36:30.370
- Take me with you.

1106
01:36:30.490 --> 01:36:31.890
- I don't have any money.
- Well, I have some.


1107
01:36:32.010 --> 01:36:34.210
- I'm going to miss my train.
Please.


1108
01:36:34.330 --> 01:36:36.530
- I know a little hotel
in Amsterdam where we can stay.


1109
01:36:36.650 --> 01:36:37.890
Come. Hurry up.

1110
01:36:50.570 --> 01:36:51.770
- Stephan!!!

1111
01:38:02.530 --> 01:38:04.210
- Never mind, mademoiselle.

1112
01:38:05.170 --> 01:38:07.010
There are hundreds like them.

1113
01:38:08.490 --> 01:38:10.850
I must explain to you,
mademoiselle...


1114
01:38:11.530 --> 01:38:14.090
...that I am an old-fashioned
sort of person.


1115
01:38:14.890 --> 01:38:17.890
You can call me conservative
or traditionalist if you like,


1116
01:38:18.010 --> 01:38:19.890
but I believe in the family.

1117
01:38:20.690 --> 01:38:23.370
Parents and grandparents,

1118
01:38:23.490 --> 01:38:25.050
grandchildren, children.

1119
01:38:25.530 --> 01:38:28.810
Nowadays...
people live in a dirty way.


1120
01:38:31.090 --> 01:38:32.610
There's no tradition.

1121
01:38:38.690 --> 01:38:40.410
There's nothing beautiful.

